Navi to Tesla requires enabling accessibility features to get some navigation destinations.

The apps to access are as follows.
- NAVER Navi

The information to be accessed is as follows.
- Destination address in the navigation app

The collected information is used for the following purposes.
- Transfer destinations to customer-owned Tesla vehicles
- Saved inside the android device to speed up


Navi to Tesla collects destination address from the navigation app, even when the app is closed or not in use.

The information collected will be used to transfer destinations via Navi to Tesla to your Tesla vehicle.
In addition, the collected information is stored inside the device to improve speed, and the information is not transmitted or stored anywhere other than for the purposes listed above.
Navi to Tesla does not collect any other information except for destination information in navigation apps.

If you do not enable accessibility features, you will not be able to use the Navi to Tesla features in the navigations listed above.
You can always disable accessibility features in your Android settings.
For some navigation apps, you can use Navi to Tesla using accessibility services.\nDetails can be found in the Settings tab.
Disable accessibility services. Navi to Tesla is not available on certain navigations.\nYou can disable the Navi to Tesla accessibility service in your Android settings.
You can grant permission again in Android\'s settings.
By adding notification permissions, you can receive related notifications when Navi to Tesla operates.
